OL,6,FThe Crown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,7,FNorth East said the victims, who were
OL,8,Fall under the age of 16 at the time of
OL,9,Fthe offences, were given drugs,
OL,10,Fcigarettes or alcohol in exchange for
OL,11,Fsex.
OL,13,FCharlotte Dennison, Head of the Rape
OL,14,Fand Serious Sexual Offences (RASSO)
OL,15,FUnit at CPS North East said: "Those
OL,16,Fconvicted today each played a part in
OL,17,Fgrooming vulnerable girls into sexual
OL,18,Factivity, with some of the victims
OL,19,Fbeing exploited by multiple men after
OL,20,Fbeing plied with drugs and alcohol.
